Description: Implements the panel CADF (Cross-sectionally Augmented 
    Dickey-Fuller) cointegration tests of Banerjee and 
    Carrion-i-Silvestre (2017) <doi:10.1111/jtsa.12234>. 
    The tests account for cross-sectional dependence through 
    Common Correlated Effects (CCE) augmentation following 
    Pesaran (2006) <doi:10.1111/j.1468-0262.2006.00692.x>. 
    Supports multiple model specifications including deterministic 
    components and up to two structural breaks in levels and/or 
    slopes. Provides individual CADF statistics, panel CIPS 
    statistics, automatic lag selection via information criteria, 
    and bootstrap critical value simulation.
